content: The Empire State Building lit up for my 22nd birthday. Reflecting on my journey, I'm determined to secure a spot in a quant trading firm. Sent out my first batch of applications today.
Had an insightful mentor session on machine learning in trading. The algorithms are complex, but I'm diving in. Also, caught up with my family; they're my rock through all this.
Analyzed past trading losses. Each mistake is a lesson. Reconnected with a peer who shared insights on loss mitigation in DeFi. Progress on my recovery strategy.
Attended a Solana meetup. The community's enthusiasm is contagious. Made some valuable contacts and even got an interview lined up with a quant firm.
Spent the past few days refining my trading algorithms with machine learning. The results are promising. Had a date, but my mind was on code—balance is key.
The interview went well. They appreciated my expertise in Rust and Solana. Now, the waiting game. Meanwhile, I'm sketching again; the city's chaos inspires.
Met with a mentor to discuss my career trajectory. They suggested focusing on niche areas within quant trading. Got a call for a second interview. Progress.
Delved into blockchain fundamentals. The tokenomics of $XVI are fascinating. Had a family dinner; their support is invaluable as I navigate this career shift.
Received an offer from a top-tier quant trading firm. The journey from Tokyo to this moment has been transformative. Time to celebrate with friends in the city.
Joined a coding bootcamp to sharpen my Rust skills. Networking with peers and learning from instructors. My career recovery strategy is in full swing.
First day at the new job. The office view is stunning, but the real beauty is the opportunity to apply machine learning in real-world trading scenarios.
Building basic dApps with $XVI. The community's support is incredible. Also, caught up with a friend who's now a blockchain developer. Our paths cross again.
Spent the weekend working on a trading strategy. Early results are encouraging. Took a break to explore the city, soaking in its energy and finding inspiration.
Presented my machine learning project at work. The feedback was constructive. Also, had a heart-to-heart with a mentor about maintaining work-life balance.
Joined a group chat with peers in the crypto space. The discussions are enriching. Also, started a new dating chapter, balancing personal growth with professional.
